source.data:
Feature: Contact details Form Tests 

    Background: To authenticate and navigate to landing page
        Given user authenticates and navigates to landing Page

    # TC-01
    Scenario: Verify the main contact section in contact details form
        Given user logs in with "acceptor" role
        Then user should view the dashboard page
        When user clicks on "Get new grant" link
        Then user should navigate to grant selection wizard
        When user selects "IT" option for the sector
        And user selects "Bring my business overseas" option for grant type
        And user selects "Market Readiness Assistance" option for grant reason
        When user intercepts the grants service in backend
        When user clicks on Apply button to apply grant
        Then user fetches grant id from grants service response
        And user should view draft application form
        When user clicks on Proceed button of draft application form
        Then user should navigate to eligibility form questions
        When user selects "Yes" option for "Is the applicant registered in Singapore?" in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "Is the applicant's group sales turnover less than or equal to S$100m " in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "Does the applicant have at least 30%" in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "that you are applying for a new market? " in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "the following statements true for this project?" in eligibility form
        When user clicks on "Next" button in eligibility form
        Then user should navigate to contact details form
        And user should view the "Main Contact Person" section fields
            |inputField|
            |Name|
            |Job Title|
            |Contact No.|
            |Email|
            |Alternate Contact Person's Email|

    #TC-02
    Scenario Outline: Verify the mailing address form is autopopulated with address when valid postal code is passed in contact details form
        Given user logs in with "acceptor" role
        Then user should view the dashboard page
        When user clicks on "Get new grant" link
        Then user should navigate to grant selection wizard
        When user selects "IT" option for the sector
        And user selects "Bring my business overseas" option for grant type
        And user selects "Market Readiness Assistance" option for grant reason
        When user intercepts the grants service in backend
        When user clicks on Apply button to apply grant
        Then user fetches grant id from grants service response
        And user should view draft application form
        When user clicks on Proceed button of draft application form
        Then user should navigate to eligibility form questions
        When user selects "Yes" option for "Is the applicant registered in Singapore?" in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "Is the applicant's group sales turnover less than or equal to S$100m " in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "Does the applicant have at least 30%" in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "that you are applying for a new market? " in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "the following statements true for this project?" in eligibility form
        When user clicks on "Next" button in eligibility form
        Then user should navigate to contact details form
        When user inputs <postalCode> in Postal Code field of mailing address section
        Then user should view "Block/House No." and "Street" fields in mailing address to be populated with values
        Examples:
        | postalCode |
        | 520337  |
        | 520339  | 

    #TC-03
    Scenario: Verify the mailing address form is autopopulated with address when invalid postal code is passed in contact details form
        Given user logs in with "acceptor" role
        Then user should view the dashboard page
        When user clicks on "Get new grant" link
        Then user should navigate to grant selection wizard
        When user selects "IT" option for the sector
        And user selects "Bring my business overseas" option for grant type
        And user selects "Market Readiness Assistance" option for grant reason
        When user intercepts the grants service in backend
        When user clicks on Apply button to apply grant
        Then user fetches grant id from grants service response
        And user should view draft application form
        When user clicks on Proceed button of draft application form
        Then user should navigate to eligibility form questions
        When user selects "Yes" option for "Is the applicant registered in Singapore?" in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "Is the applicant's group sales turnover less than or equal to S$100m " in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "Does the applicant have at least 30%" in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "that you are applying for a new market? " in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "the following statements true for this project?" in eligibility form
        When user clicks on "Next" button in eligibility form
        Then user should navigate to contact details form
        When user inputs 999999 in Postal Code field of mailing address section
        Then user should be prompted with "postalCodeNotFound" message below the Postal Code field

    #TC-04
    Scenario: Verify the mailing address form is autopopulated with address when user clicks on company profile address checkbox
        Given user logs in with "acceptor" role
        Then user should view the dashboard page
        When user clicks on "Get new grant" link
        Then user should navigate to grant selection wizard
        When user selects "IT" option for the sector
        And user selects "Bring my business overseas" option for grant type
        And user selects "Market Readiness Assistance" option for grant reason
        When user intercepts the grants service in backend
        When user clicks on Apply button to apply grant
        Then user fetches grant id from grants service response
        And user should view draft application form
        When user clicks on Proceed button of draft application form
        Then user should navigate to eligibility form questions
        When user selects "Yes" option for "Is the applicant registered in Singapore?" in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "Is the applicant's group sales turnover less than or equal to S$100m " in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "Does the applicant have at least 30%" in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "that you are applying for a new market? " in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "the following statements true for this project?" in eligibility form
        When user clicks on "Next" button in eligibility form
        Then user should navigate to contact details form
        When user clicks on "Same as registered address" checkbox in contact details section
        Then user should view "Block/House No." and "Street" fields in mailing address to be populated with values

    # TC-05
    Scenario: Verify the Letter of offer addressee section in contact details form
        Given user logs in with "acceptor" role
        Then user should view the dashboard page
        When user clicks on "Get new grant" link
        Then user should navigate to grant selection wizard
        When user selects "IT" option for the sector
        And user selects "Bring my business overseas" option for grant type
        And user selects "Market Readiness Assistance" option for grant reason
        When user intercepts the grants service in backend
        When user clicks on Apply button to apply grant
        Then user fetches grant id from grants service response
        And user should view draft application form
        When user clicks on Proceed button of draft application form
        Then user should navigate to eligibility form questions
        When user selects "Yes" option for "Is the applicant registered in Singapore?" in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "Is the applicant's group sales turnover less than or equal to S$100m " in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "Does the applicant have at least 30%" in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "that you are applying for a new market? " in eligibility form
        And user selects "Yes" option for "the following statements true for this project?" in eligibility form
        When user clicks on "Next" button in eligibility form
        Then user should navigate to contact details form
        And user should view the "Letter Of Offer Addressee" section fields
            |inputField|
            |Name|
            |Job Title|
            |Email|
